HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 122
BY REPRESENTATIVE NEWELL
A RESOLUTION
To commend Heaven Riley Breaux for being named Miss Louisiana Teen USA.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Heaven Riley Breaux on her outstanding
achievements and to commend her for being named Miss Louisiana Teen USA; and
WHEREAS, Heaven is an eleventh-grade student and a varsity cheerleader at
Lafayette Renaissance Charter Academy; she is the daughter of Riley and Yolanda Breaux
of Lafayette, Louisiana, and the youngest sibling of Justyn and Jasen Breaux; and
WHEREAS, Heaven, whose life is deeply rooted in faith and family, serves as a
junior usher under the leadership of Reverend Chad Ned at Mt. Pilgrim Baptist Church in
Opelousas, Louisiana; and
WHEREAS, Heaven found inspiration in the world of pageantry at early age,
watching pageants alongside her mother; after witnessing Miss South Africa's crowning as
Miss Universe in 2019, she decided to step onto the stage and transform her admiration into
ambition; and
WHEREAS, Heaven's journey in pageants is defined by growth, discipline, and
purpose; she has earned numerous titles over the years, including Our Little Miss State
Preteen Queen, Miss Lafayette Louisiana Preteen USA, Miss Pelican State Preteen, Miss
Opelousas Teen USA, and Miss Greater Baton Rouge Teen USA; and
WHEREAS, Heaven was most recently crowned Miss Louisiana Teen USA, and
each stage of her journey has strengthened her confidence and commitment to using her
platform to make a positive impact on the community; and
WHEREAS, Heaven is the founder of Bows of Confidence, which reflects her
passion for empowering young girls to embrace their individuality, build self worth, and lead
with confidence; she is active in mentorship and community initiatives, through which she
strives to create spaces where every girl feels seen, valued, and empowered to shine; and
